column1: # Original dataset (HOTELLING_NEI_v2_2014_from_CDBs_18sep2017_v0.csv) provided by Allison DenBleyker (ERG)
# Includes state-submitted data and EPA defaults as stored in MOVES CDBs.
# Dataset HOTELLING_NEI_v2_2014_candidate_20170630 contains more information about the background of that dataset.
# This dataset is based on the "from_CDBs" dataset and includes additional adjustments to HOTELLING
column2: based on truck stop parking space data.

column1: # Many counties had hotelling hours greater than the number of available parking spaces * the number of hours in a year

column2: hotelling hours were adjusted downward so that they do not exceed the theoretical maximum based on the number of parking spaces

column1: #   with 12 parking spaces in each county as the minimum to account for missing/incomplete truck stop data.
# A few high activity counties had a custom adjustment factor applied instead of the default based on analysis by Alison Eyth
#   2014v2 hotelling by county versus truck stop parking_102717.xlsx
# The result is an approximately 1/3 reduction in nationwide HOTELLING hours.
